OL,3,C'They were heroes': The Teesside
OL,4,Cvolunteers who fought in the Spanish
OL,5,CCivil War
OL,7,FFranco's forces were backed by Adolf
OL,8,FHitler's Nazi Germany and Benito
OL,9,FMussolini's fascist Italy. Because of
OL,10,Fthe international context and issues,
OL,11,Fthe civil war is often seen as the
OL,12,F'first battle' of the Second World
OL,13,FWar, which followed.
OL,15,FThirty Teesside men joined the
OL,16,FInternational Brigade, to fight
OL,17,Fagainst General Franco's forces. Nine
OL,18,Fof them lost their lives.
OL,20,FPeople gathered at Heugh Battery
OL,21,FMuseum today to remember them.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/6
